RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 105. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 36500. (PLUS UP TO $7,300 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, STATE BRED OR TRIAL SINCE OCTOBER 29, 2022 OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 30, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since October 30, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Maiden Or Claiming Races Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLD PILOT taken well in hand to trail early, dropped to the rail to begin a sustained rally from the three-eights pole, split horses in upper stretch and finished gamely to prevail at the wire. KOKOKOMO reserved off the pacesetters, commenced an early drive into the turn, circled the field, drifted out in the lane while under strong urging and came up just short. BIZZY LEGS sped to the lead into the first turn up the fence, set a well rated pace and opened a clear advantage at the head of the lane but was no match for the top two. TIZ LIFE stalked the pace from three wide to the quarter pole in striking position and lacked a late response when put to a drive. FLASH OF MISCHIEF pressed the pace from between horses to the top of the stretch and was injured when making a move for the lead and was vanned off.

ENTRY.NAME: Bizzy Legs
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, well rated, no answer

ENTRY.NAME: Flash of Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace between, rallied, injured vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Life
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, well positioned, no response

ENTRY.NAME: Kokokomo
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, early drive, circled, drifted out lane, just missed

ENTRY.NAME: Gold Pilot
ENTRY.COMMENT: in hand, trailed, inside move, split horses, driving, gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 17500. (PLUS UP TO $875 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 30, 2022 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORT HOOD was under a steady drive to duel for the lead while two wide, then inched away on the turn to kick clear in the upper stretch and prevail under a strong hand drive. NIGHTWIND chased the pace while two wide, then came out four wide to duel for the place position with an inner rival down the lane and was closing strong to be up just in time. PLAIN TAP WATER chased the pace from the inside into the turn, then closed well down the lane while dueling for the place prize and just missed it in the end. ATTILA THE DUN raced closed behind the field while two wide down the backstretch and into the turn then bid mildly in the stretch but it was not enough in the end. JUST HANGIN RIDGE dueled for the lead from the inside into the turn, was hard used and tired in the stretch. SLIM JIMMY raced behind the field along the inside, then gradually faded and was no rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, closed well stretch, just missed 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2w, rallied 4w upper, close strong, up 4 place

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled inside, hard drive turn, used up, tired late

ENTRY.COMMENT: duel 2 wide, steady drive, kicked clear upper, driving

ENTRY.COMMENT: faded inside, no rally

ENTRY.COMMENT: raced 2 wide, evenly turn, mild bid late, not enough

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvisable by manageme nt to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MADAMOUSSEPOUSSE dueled from between horses on the early pace, took command turning for home and drew off in convincing fashion as a clear winner. GLORY O stalked the pace to the turn, loomed up at the quarter pole and finished willingly as second best. LIBBIES BABY raced up the rail inside the leaders, backed out of the pace duel at the three-eights pole and finished evenly to gain the show. MASTER SOM rushed up from between rivals to take the lead, dueled with the winner in the turn and gave way down the lane. BALI DOVE (FR) reserved off the pace near the rear of the field and failed to respond when called upon. TRICKY CARLA broke well, dropped to the rear of the field and never threatened. JUDY'S CUSTARD broke inward brushing her rival leaving the gate, showed brief speed and steadily faded to the rear.

(PLUS UP TO $7,100 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE SINCE JANUARY 1, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 11 9 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 28 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Maiden, Claiming, Or Starter Races Not Considered In Allowances). Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPRESSED pressed the pace while two wide into the turn, vied for the lead around the quarter pole then edged clear in the late stretch and was ridden out under a confident hand ride. AVAILABLE STAR was bumped at the start then trailed behind the field into the turn, dug in gamely in the early stretch then closed with fire while splitting rivals along the way and was second best in the end. EMPIRE OF GOLD pressed the pace from the three path into the turn, vied for the lead in the early stretch, then continued to close gamely till the end just missing the place prize. GOOD SCOUT sped to the front to take command around the four and a half pole, then lead the way into the turn, vied to keep the lead in the early stretch but could not retain bid and gave way in the end. PICKENS stalked the pace while four wide then bid on the turn but came up evenly in the stretch. SILVER WINGS bumped foe at the start then tracked the pace from the inside, bid on the turn but came up empty in the end and needed more.

VA VOOM tracked the pace into the turn, moved up the fence to mount a challenge and failed to gain ground late. BOBBIE O reserved off the early pace, responded when asked with a steady mild rally. EMMYLOU SQUALL pressed the pacesetter to the quarter pole and weakened down the stretch. MISCHIEF ANGEL raced mid-pack, went evenly and never was a threat. PURRFECT MOON raced near the rear of the field throughout as a non-factor. PERFECT MESA showed brief speed to be in early contention and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SENSEOFEXCELLENCE vied for the lead from the two path, gained command entering the turn, then drew clear in the early stretch and was kept to task till the end. CADEAU DE PAIX chased the pace while four wide into the turn, then rallied gamely in the upper stretch to close fastest down the lane for the place prize. RING ME DARLING raced between rivals then bid while two wide on the turn to rally in the late stretch and was best for show in the end. RUMPUS vied for the lead from the inside then settled back on the turn, came out four wide in the early stretch to rally and was closing well in the end. BLUEBERRY EYES settled along the inside into the turn then menaced in the early stretch to close willingly in the final furlong. SWEET SLEW settled while four wide, then bid on the turn to rally in late stretch but it was too little too late. TELLING THYME raced while three deep in the second group of rivals, then rallied on turn into the stretch but came up empty in the end. MAINLINE was moving up while five wide to press the pace from the three path throughout the turn, was hard used and gave way in the lane. SWEET ADELINE was in a hard drive to bid for the lead while three wide, then pressed the pace throughout the turn from the two path, was used up and weakened in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO $2,600 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAZI moved up the fence to duel for the early lead leaving the chute, battled through the turn on the lead, edged away in the lane to persevere in a determined drive. TEXAS TIDELANDS pressed the pace from three wide through the turn to seriously threaten turning for home, could not gain on the winner, was passed by rival in the upper stretch and came on again for the place. ITS MY MONEY TOO reserved off the early leaders, circled four wide in the turn to loom boldly at the top of the lane, closed to be second mid-stretch and hung late to give up the place. ITS A GEE THING tracked the pacesetters to the turn, ranged up behind a wall of horses at the quarter pole and finished willingly to be best of the rest. INDY LOVER raced in the second flight on the outside and went evenly. GANGSTER RAP showed brief speed to be well positioned for the first quarter, dropped back in the field and passed tiring rivals down the stretch. JIBE broke alertly to take the lead, dueled for three-eighths and steadily faded. WILD PROSPECT trailed the field early, made a brief bid in the turn up the rail and flattened out. CHEROKEE SUMMER was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $3,000 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $20,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Black Fence Racing Stables and Caldwell J R

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUL SACRIFICE pressed the pace from the inside, then dueled with the pace setter throughout the turn, dug in gamely in the early stretch to kick clear of that rival and held on well till the end. STAR SAILOR saved ground down the backstretch while racing along the inside, then bid on the turn, rallied in the upper stretch and was closing strong to be up for the place prize. TREASURE COAST was under an easy stride to stalk the pace from the three path down the backstretch and throughout the turn, then rallied at the top of the lane to close well and was out finished for place in the end. BIG STORY was under a steady drive to chase the pace from the inside down the first half and into the turn then made a mild bid in the stretch but came up empty in the end. CALIPARI settled along the inside down the backstretch and into the turn, then angled out seven wide in the early stretch to rally but it was too little too late. AMERICAN SMOOTH chased the pace while three wide, made a mild bid on the from the four path then continued to close evenly throughout the stretch. JERSEY JIM lead the way down the backstretch while two wide, then dueled with an inner rival to keep the lead throughout the turn, was used up and gave way in the end. CALARI BLUECAT chased the pace while two wide, was in hard drive throughout the turn, was used up then flattened out in the stretch. BRAZIL NUT was unhurried early then bid mildly from the three path on the turn and was no menace. GOLD DECLARATION was out run and no factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $1,650 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvi sable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISSINGYOUCRAZY sped to the lead into the first turn, set a well measured, comfortable pace down the backstretch, opened her advantage into the turn and drew off as much best. GOLD MEMORIES broke a step slow, settled into stride, steadily advanced on the outside to the turn, rallied four wide and finished well to be a clear second best. LA VALEDORA tracked the pace from the fence down the backside, mounted a bid in the turn, could not gain on the leader, was outkicked for the place but finished willingly as the best of the rest. BLOOD ORANGE reserved off the lead for the run to the turn, circled wide and made a steady late gain through the stretch. MEMORABLE FLIGHT pressed the winner to the quarter pole and gave way down the lane. BLINGONMERCURY was prominently placed in striking position and failed to rally finishing evenly. PHARME'S PHINALE stalked the pace for a half mile and came up empty. S S TURBINIA was never a factor. RUBY SOHO was no threat and virtually eased to the wire.
